This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it discusses sparsity-based methods that are widely used in machine learning. It may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for computing a projection onto a constraint set. Additionally, it may belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it discusses optimization methods, cs.IT (Information Theory) as it mentions graph sparsity, and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it discusses hierarchical sparsity.
